Rizal: The struggle grows darker. Perhaps the story must become darker as well.
Reformist: You are writing another novel?
Rizal: Yes. It will reveal the anger and frustration of our people.
Reformist: The first book shook the colony. This one may shake it even more.
Rizal: Sometimes a nation must confront its pain before it can heal.
"Spanish Official": Señor Rizal, your writings criticize the government.
Rizal: I criticize injustice, not Spain itself.
"Spanish Official": Your words influence many Filipinos.
Rizal: If my words awaken them, then they serve their purpose.
Reformist: When will the book be finished?
Rizal: Soon. And when it is published, the world will understand our struggle.